{
  "stem": "13584.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So the soldiers used to carry on their shoulders not only their rifle, but also they used to carry the-- the mine-throwers, you know.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't know how to say it right in-- in-- in English.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's-- it's on wheels that you are putting some-- some, you know, the big, big bullets or whatever.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And you're hiding your head, and it shoots-- shoot out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My daddy was-- my father was in this-- this unit.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he was-- because it was so heavy, his stomach went down.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So since-- since he died, he had problems with his stomach, with ulcers, with everything from the war.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But he never-- this I have to-- I have to say it, that even though in Russia a lot of Jews changed their names, my father never changed his name.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "His name was always Szlomo in-- in Russia, in Poland.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "In Russia, they also ask for not only first name and last name, but also patronymic, patronymic.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And since his father was Yankev, Yankev, he used to call himself Szlomo [?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Yankevevich ?] Szczupak.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Never changed-- never changed his Jewishness, never for-- for a second.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was because of the war, because of the Russians learned what's happened to the Jewish population, what's happened everywhere Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Perhaps this.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I remember anti-Semitic outbursts.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For example, if I wanted to go outside in Russia-- before even we found out my father and during when my father came, you know.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I-- very often boys knew with that-- oh, oh, Jew, oh, Jew, you-- you-- you this [? kind of ?] SOB, you Jew.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they-- once even I got hit by-- by-- by-- by a boy because I was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
